4:
Antipode Lance... Bend your will to
my own.
12: Is that... light from the surface world?!
16:
We should be connected to a
Doomsday Lance on the surface
now—though travel is only possible
from this direction. Let's proceed as
planned.
20:
I shall return to the Silver Woods and
join my forces on the frontlines.
23:
It's possible there are survivors from
the Resistance as well. I will rally
them, but...
28:
But we don't stand a chance against
the Lord of Shadow. He can't be
beaten...
31:
His power is beyond compare. He
has grown even stronger than when
he and I last fought.
33:
Indeed... If even the Witch of Burning
Blood herself fell before him, the
situation is quite dire.
36:
But our encounter with him was not
for naught. And after this previous
battle, I'm all but certain...
38:
It's likely the Lord of Shadow... is
himself a daemon.
46:
Given how the Antipode Lance
made quick work of daemons, it's
possible that it might be effective
against the Lord of Shadow as well.
50:
I'm going to venture down into the
abyss.
57:
Yes. There lies the true source of the
Lord of Shadow's power. Of his
immortality.
With the Antipode Lance, I should be
able to sever the connection.
59: Stella, I'll need your help to do this.
67:
She's a child, damn you! Why do you
insist on getting her and Alk involved
every step of the way? I won't let you—
70:
Because it DOES involve you.
Remember the World Flipper, stolen
from Excelion? It could be there.
73:
You could complete the starchart
and finally restore yourself to what
you were before—to be the
Champion once again.
77:
Drop the act, Adjudicus. It's clear
that you need Stella and are willing
to do and say whatever it takes to
get her to go with you!
82: I will accompany him into the abyss.
86:
Princess, what are you saying?! You
can't do something as foolhardy as
that..
89:
You... You belong on the surface,
with your people! Please... I can't lose
you too...
93:
Champion Light, do not forget... I am
not Princess Lily!
96:
I'm sorry. I hope you can find it in
your heart to understand.
98:
Everything that happens from here
on out... It will likely decide the fate
of the entire world.
100:
I do not wish to return to my
homeland and rule as a powerless
figurehead. I must win my people's
favor and respect by fighting on
their behalf, here.
103:
Estariel. Someone will need to
bolster the Resistance forces and
keep an eye out on the fiend rebels,
to make sure they don't do anything
out of line.
106: Can I ask these things of you?
113:
But of course.
The fate of our world is in your
hands, King of Man.
116:
Take heed of Adjudicus. His left eye
bears the same scent as the
daemons.
119:
Open the gate. I will buy you the
precious time you need.
122:
Heh. You know, as we stand here on
the precipice of a momentous
occasion, an amusing thought
comes to mind. Did I ever tell you
the origin of my name?
125:
"Estar" means "hope" in the Elvish
tongue... Yet now it seems all the
hopes of our people are placed in
you, Lilith Stratos. I pray the burden
is not too heavy.
129: I shall do my best to bear it, Estariel.
133:
And Stella... Do not think that we
elves have forgotten the songs of
blessing that the stars bestowed
upon us. We are forever grateful.
135:
May you have fortune in the battles
to come.
145:
She's ascended to the surface. We,
however, are bound in the opposite
direction.
165:
I understand... But, come back alive,
do you hear?! No matter what!
168:
Lord Adjudicus! I beg you!
Protect these two! Keep them safe.
180:
I lost track of time... How long have
we been falling like this?
182:
Just how deep does this go? It feels
like we've sunk a hundred times the
height of one of those lances. It
doesn't make sense.
186:
You're right... When you put it that
way, this place is pretty similar to
the Kaleidoscope, isn't it?
189:
Think of this place as a chasm
carved into the world.
192:
That's precisely why the World
Flipper was stolen from
Pandemonium. To cut the abyss off
from the remaining worlds.
194:
But your world, Purger, is an
exception. It was created by the
Overlords as a sort of lid, used to
shut in our world.
202:
Have you managed to regain any of
your memories, Stella?
208:
The Overlords are the beings who
created both me and the Champion.
214:
Created the Champion? Wh-what
do you mean?
218: What on earth are these things?!
221:
No doubt they're just like you,
Champion—creations of the
Overlords.
